  "texts": [
    "In the pre-processing phase, two clip limits were used, as shown in Fig. 2.",
    "Detection phaseAt this phase, You Look Only Once (YOLO) model has been selected for mass detection.",
    "YOLO is a well-known object detection architecture known as a single-shot detector, as the image is processed in one shot to detect multiple objects within it.",
    "One of the advantages of YOLO is looking at the complete image, which means less information loss, and this is considered one of the crucial points that affect the interpretation of medical images.",
    "Furthermore, the detection and classification are done simultaneously, making the YOLO faster than other detectors."
  ],
